result.execSummary:
The defendant Patricia A Nunway was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fraud/Innkeeper,etc-Nonpayment (<=$2500) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.21(1m)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Intentionally Abuse Hazardous Substance [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.316(2)(b).
  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Joint and several with co-defendant's Dancia McGeshick (16CM97) and Lianne soman (16CF128).

The defendant must obtain her GED/HSED.

The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.

The defendant may not consume or possess alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns.

The defendant may not have any contact with Main Street Inn, Crandon, WI or enter on to the premises of Main Street Inn, Crandon, WI.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Patricia A Nunway in court with attorney Chad Lynch.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 10:05 AM. Called 16CM98 and 16CT05. State - here for change of plea - resolved. Court provided with plea questionnaires for each case by Lynch. State - have complied with victim notification requirements - 16CT05 - plead g/nc to only count as alleged, court costs and 60 days jail; 16CM98 - plead g/nc to counts #1, #2, #3 and #6 as alleged, dismiss and read in remaining counts; counts #1 and #3 - 2 years probation, #2 and #6 - 60 days jail on each counts - concurrent to each other and to other jail but the probation would be running consecutive to 16CT05, conditions include: AODA and follow thru, restittution of $214.50, joint and severally with co-defendants with VW surcharge of $21.45 for a total restitution amount of $235.95 (Main Street Inn - Crandon), maintain absolute sobriety, no possession and no entry, employment/school, 200 hours of community service, no contact with victim (Main Street Inn - Crandon, WI). Lynch and Nunway agree accept there is a discrepency in the amount of restitution on the written offer as to what was stated. State agrees and the amount stated is the correct amount. Court - 16CM98 - dismisses and reads in counts #4, #5 and #7. On 16CM98 - Nunway pleads NC to counts #1, #2, #3 and #6 as alleged. On 16CT05 - Nunway pleads NC to only count. Court has plea questionnaire and notices an error on count #1 of16CM98 in regards to repeater allegation. Lynch responds, does not believe a repeater allegation can be on that count. State not objecting and deletes repeater enhancement. Court amends count #1 on 16CM98 to delete the repeater allegation. Nunway still pleads NC to the amended count #1. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently wiaved her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts pleas, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Lynch makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendations. Nunway withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 16CT05 - costs - take bond posted - remainder due in 60 days/CO, 60 days in FC jail - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3) - report today; 16CM98 - counts #1 and #3 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years - concurrent to each other but consecutive to jail time on 16CT05, with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, restitution of $235.95 - joint and several with co-defendants - paid thru probation, 200 hours of community service, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, obtain GED, no contact with Main Street Inn or enter onto the premises of Main Street Inn; counts #2 and #6 - costs on each count - paid in 180 days/CO, 60 days jail on each count - concurrent to each other and to jail time on 16CT05 - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(d) - report today - credit for 10 days, submit DNA sample, right to appeal, adjourned.
Plea/sentencing hearing on October 31, 2016 at 09:15 am.
Jury trial on November 3, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Patricia A Nunway in court with attorney Chad Lynch.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:10 PM. Called 16CM98 and 16CT05. Lynch - not resolved - puts offer on the record, on 16CM98 - defendant would plead to counts #1, #2, #3, and #6 as alleged, dismiss remaining counts, for counts #1 and #3 - place on probation for 2 years and on counts #2 and #6 - 90 days jail on each count, concurrent to each other. Lynch has gone over Frye with the defendant. Court continues bond, sets both matters for JT on 11/3/16 at 8:30 AM. Agreement on 16CT05 - plead to only count as alleged with 60 days in FC jail and court costs.
Final pre-trial on August 24, 2016 at 02:00 pm.
Final pre-trial on August 17, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
Final pre-trial on July 27, 2016 at 10:15 am.

Defendant Patricia A Nunway in court with attorney Chad Lynch.  Defendant Patricia A Nunway in custody and appears via video from FOSO.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 10:02 AM. Called 16CM98 (INIT) and 16CT05 (BBR). Nunway does not have complaint in 16CM98. Court reads charges and penalties. Lynch and Nunway understand charges and penalties. Lynch waives further reading, enters NG pleas to all counts on this matter, set for FPT. Lynch wants to be heard on the forfeiture of the bond on 16CT05 - states his objection to the forfeiture of that bond and asks that the bond not be forfeited. State - defers to the court. Court - will accept Lynch's argument and sets aside the forfeiture and sets bond on both matters to $800.00 cash total. Additional discussion on bond. Court - bond - $300.00 cash on 16CT05, 16CM98 - $2000.00 signature bond, no consumption of alcohol on both cases.  Final pre-trial scheduled for July 27, 2016 at 10:15 am.
